commit.message: test_Exceptions: add tests for CardRequestTimeoutException

Exceptions: fix a bug with CardRequestTimeoutException

Thanks to James E. A. for the bug report
" TypeError: CardRequestTimeoutException.__init__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'hresult' #165 "
Closes: https://github.com/LudovicRousseau/pyscard/issues/165

test: check the test SCARDDWORDARG is an integer

Test the code that checks SCARDDWORDARG is of the expected type
(integer).

Fix C compiler warnings

SCARDDWORDARG is an "uint32_t" or "unsigned long". So "-1" should be casted to
avoid a C compiler warnings.

smartcard/scard/scard_wrap.c:4221:12: warning: comparison of integers of different signs: 'int' and 'SCARDDWORDARG' (aka 'unsigned int') [-Wsign-compare]
    if (-1 == arg2)
        ~~ ^  ~~~~
smartcard/scard/scard_wrap.c:4284:12: warning: comparison of integers of different signs: 'int' and 'SCARDDWORDARG' (aka 'unsigned int') [-Wsign-compare]
    if (-1 == arg2)
        ~~ ^  ~~~~
[etc...]

Thanks to Tomasz Kłoczko for the bug report
" 2.0.8: compile time warnings #164 "
Closes: https://github.com/LudovicRousseau/pyscard/issues/164

Make CardMonitor() thread safe

We had a TOCTOU bug in the handling of CardMonitor.instance field.
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use

Thanks to Lars Lengersdorf for the bug reprot
" pyscard seems to be not thread save #162 "
Fixes: https://github.com/LudovicRousseau/pyscard/issues/162
